cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.DS, cs.NE 

This paper discusses the use of ensembles in machine learning, which is a common topic in the subfield of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper specifically focuses on the role of diversity in ensembles, which is relevant to the subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computer vision (cs.CV) where ensembles are commonly used. The paper also discusses the measurement of diversity, which is related to the subfield of data science (cs.DS). Finally, the paper proposes a pruning method for ensembles, which is relevant to the subfield of neural networks (cs.NE) where pruning is a common technique.
